Comment: I still don't have much of an opening repertoire.  Need to work on that.  This game, my poor opening put me at a disadvantage beginning at about move 7.  Well, it isn't exactly a poor knowledge of openings but rather a few bad decisions during the opening that got me in to trouble early in this game.
Black plays the King's Indian, East Indian defense (I don't know this from experience or study. I looked it up).  Seems to be a variation of the Reti system or Benko opening, except in reverse.
